<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer11191850231076582434">Jedediah Berry was raised in the Hudson Valley region of New York State. His first novel, <i>The Manual of Detection</i>, received the Crawford Fantasy Award and the Dashiell Hammett Prize, and his short stories have appeared in anthologies including <i>Best New American Voices</i> and <i>Best American Fantasy</i>. He lives in Western Massachusetts.<br/><br/>&quot;Jedediah Berry knows magic. <i>The Manual of Detection</i> combines the intr</span>
  <span id="freeText11191850231076582434" style="display:none">Jedediah Berry was raised in the Hudson Valley region of New York State. His first novel, <i>The Manual of Detection</i>, received the Crawford Fantasy Award and the Dashiell Hammett Prize, and his short stories have appeared in anthologies including <i>Best New American Voices</i> and <i>Best American Fantasy</i>. He lives in Western Massachusetts.<br /><br />"Jedediah Berry knows magic. <i>The Manual of Detection</i> combines the intricacy and thoughtfulness of Borges and Kafka with the page-turning excitement of a detective thriller.... It made me laugh, thrill, think, and wonder."—<b>Hannah Tinti</b>, author of <i>The Good Thief</i><br /></span>
